# Experimental Approach

## Setup

Two identical systems:

- System A: Conventional excitation (DC or simple pulsed)
- System B: SRC-based excitation (structured waveform + optional RLC)

## Conditions

- identical geometry
- identical medium
- identical temperature
- identical input power

## Measurements

- Voltage (U)
- Current (I)
- Power (P)
- Gas production rate (ml/min)
- Temperature (T)

Optional:
- Phase difference (Δφ)
- Impedance

## Goal

Identify measurable differences in:

- efficiency
- stability
- loss behavior

## Important Constraint

The excitation method must be the only variable.
